cs.NE, cs.CB, cs.SI, cs.ET, cs.BI 

This paper involves the study of interactions between voltage pulses in actin filaments, which is related to the field of computational neuroscience and neural networks (cs.NE). The use of logical gates and half-adders also suggests a connection to the field of computer engineering and digital circuits (cs.CB). The concept of information transmission and processing in actin networks may also fall under the category of signal processing (cs.SI). Additionally, the study of actin filaments and their role in cellular processes may be relevant to the field of emerging technologies (cs.ET) and bioinformatics (cs.BI).
